ciscoAuthorizationStatsMibModule.name: ciscoAuthorizationStatsMibModule

revisions.description: The initial version of this MIB.

ciscoAuthorizationStatsMibModule.contactinfo: Cisco Systems 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-cvpn3000@cisco.com
ciscoAuthorizationStatsMibModule.description: The Cisco User Authorization Statistics MIB models counters and objects that are of management interest.

cAuthorizationStatsTable.name: cAuthorizationStatsTable
cAuthorizationStatsTable.description: The list of servers that may be queried for authorization attributes for connecting IPSec tunnel users.

cAuthorizationStatsEntry.name: cAuthorizationStatsEntry
cAuthorizationStatsEntry.description: An entry in the cAuthorizationStatsTable. These entries are created or destroyed whenever an authorization server connection is added or removed via one of the management interfaces to the tunnel server.

cAuthorizServerIndex.name: cAuthorizServerIndex
cAuthorizServerIndex.description: The unique number used as the index for this row.

cAuthorizServerAddressType.name: cAuthorizServerAddressType
cAuthorizServerAddressType.description: The type of Internet address used by this entry.

cAuthorizServerAddress.name: cAuthorizServerAddress
cAuthorizServerAddress.description: The IP address of the authorization server whose statistics are being reported.

cAuthorizClientServerPortNum.name: cAuthorizClientServerPortNum
cAuthorizClientServerPortNum.description: The UDP The port on the server to which authorization requests are directed.

cAuthorizClientRoundTripTime.name: cAuthorizClientRoundTripTime
cAuthorizClientRoundTripTime.description: The time interval between the most recent Access-Reply/Access-Challenge and the Access-Request.

cAuthorizClientAccessRequests.name: cAuthorizClientAccessRequests
cAuthorizClientAccessRequests.description: The total number of Access-Request packets sent to authorization server since client start-up. This does not include retransmissions.

cAuthorizClientAccessRetrans.name: cAuthorizClientAccessRetrans
cAuthorizClientAccessRetrans.description: The total number of Access-Request packets retransmitted to authorization server since client start-up.

cAuthorizClientAccessAccepts.name: cAuthorizClientAccessAccepts
cAuthorizClientAccessAccepts.description: The total number of Access-Accept packets received by authorization server since client start-up.

cAuthorizClientAccessRejects.name: cAuthorizClientAccessRejects
cAuthorizClientAccessRejects.description: The total number of Access-Reject packets received by authorization server since client start-up.

cAuthorizClientAccessChallenges.name: cAuthorizClientAccessChallenges
cAuthorizClientAccessChallenges.description: The total number of Access-Challenge packets received by authorization server since client start-up.

cAuthorizClientMalAccessResps.name: cAuthorizClientMalAccessResps
cAuthorizClientMalAccessResps.description: The total number of malformed Access-Response packets received by authoriztion server since client start-up. Malformed packets include packets with an invalid length. Bad authenticators or Signature attributes are not included as malformed access responses.

cAuthorizClientBadAuthenticates.name: cAuthorizClientBadAuthenticates
cAuthorizClientBadAuthenticates.description: The total number of Access-Response packets containing invalid authenticators or Signature attributes received by authorization server since client start-up.

cAuthorizClientPendingRequests.name: cAuthorizClientPendingRequests
cAuthorizClientPendingRequests.description: The total number of Access-Request packets destined for authorization server that have not yet timed out or received a response. This variable is incremented when an Access-Request is sent and decremented due to receipt of an Access-Reply or Access-Challenge, a timeout or retransmission.

cAuthorizClientTimeouts.name: cAuthorizClientTimeouts
cAuthorizClientTimeouts.description: The total number of timeouts to authorization server since client startup. After a timeout the client may retry to the same server, send to a different server, or give up. A retry to the same server is counted as a retransmit as well as a timeout. A send to a different server is counted as a Request as well as a timeout.

cAuthorizClientUnknownTypes.name: cAuthorizClientUnknownTypes
cAuthorizClientUnknownTypes.description: The total number of unknown type packets received by authorization server since client start-up.

cAuthorizServerGroupId.name: cAuthorizServerGroupId
cAuthorizServerGroupId.description: The Id of user group associated with authorization server. The group ID is an integer value assigned by the tunnel server. Group ID 0 is a special value used to refer all gorups.

cAuthorizationMIBCompliance.name: cAuthorizationMIBCompliance
cAuthorizationMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for authorization clients implementing the Authorization Client MIB.

cAuthorizationClientMIBGroup.name: cAuthorizationClientMIBGroup
cAuthorizationClientMIBGroup.description: The basic collection of objects providing management of Authorization Clients.
